comment._content: There is a possible in the 1911 census - Thomas Henry O'Brien, aged 48, born Cork, Ireland, Major Retired Infantry, living at Newnham Croft, near Wallingford, Berkshire, with his wife - Elizabeth, aged 39, born London, children - Robert Alfred, aged 8, born London and Sheila Edith Pauline, aged 7, born Preston, Lancashire and three servants. He had been married for 11 years and had 3 children of whom 1 had died.
